        "source_file": "notes/harder_batch22_web_compute.md",
        "content": "### EP-1017\n- Quick literature check:\n  - Open for the sharpened `k>n^2/4` question; page records complete `K_4`-free additive-triangle result (Gyori--Keszegh 2017).\n- Finite compute signal:\n  - In explicit `K_4`-free constructions with `e = floor(n^2/4)+q`, greedy edge-disjoint triangle packing reached at least `q` in tested cases.\n- Interpretation:\n  - Finite construction checks align with the known `K_4`-free phenomenon, without resolving the full clique-partition function."
      }
    ],
    "script_sources": [
      {
        "source_file": "scripts/harder_batch22_quick_compute.mjs",
        "heading": "edge-disjoint triangle packing in K4-free graphs above n^2/4 via explicit constructions.",
        "content": "// EP-1017: edge-disjoint triangle packing in K4-free graphs above n^2/4 via explicit constructions.\n{\n  const rng = makeRng(20260304 ^ 1017);\n  const rows = [];\n  for (const n of [20, 26, 32]) {\n    const base = Math.floor((n * n) / 4);\n    for (const q of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) {\n      const G = buildBipartitePlusInternalEdges(n, q, rng);\n      const { best, triangle_count } = greedyEdgeDisjointTrianglePacking(G.adj, rng, 60);\n      rows.push({\n        n,\n        edges: G.m,\n        floor_n2_over_4: base,\n        q_above_threshold: G.m - base,\n        total_triangles_in_graph: triangle_count,\n        best_greedy_edge_disjoint_triangles_found: best,\n        verifies_best_ge_q_in_greedy_trials: best >= q,\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  out.results.ep1017 = {\n    description: 'Finite exact packing checks for K4-free constructions with edges floor(n^2/4)+q.',\n    rows,\n  };\n}"
      }
    ],
